              <h3>Pyro</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="class-details-block merc-bullets">
              <ul>
                <li>
                  <strong>HEAT SYSTEM:</strong> Flames now more accurately distinguish
                  between dense clumps of fire and stray particles, scaling down by
                  their heat over time as they become stale.
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <em>
                        We weren't entirely satisfied with the accuracy rework
                        from our last update, though it was an improvement, it
                        did not measure flame damage as accurately as possible
                        and thus wasn't as strict about keeping flames on a
                        target as we had hoped. This new system should alleviate
                        those concerns, rewarding aim while still keeping the
                        identity of the Flame Thrower unique.
                      </em>
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Updated the heat density/accuracy mechanic to take into
                      consideration stale/lingering flames properly. Clusters of
                      flames do different damage compared to smaller single
                      flame puffs, according to the cumulative age/heat of the
                      whole group rather than the newest flame, while still
                      appropriately rewarding tracking even at long range.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Fixed flames colliding with enemies twice every tick
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Fixed an exploit that allowed users to maintain full
                      accuracy by puffing short bursts of the Flamethrower
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Fixed alignment with tickrate that was causing
                      inconsistent application of damage
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li>
                  Fixed some last few airblast reflection issues
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      Fixed reflected Dragon's Fury projectiles not retaining
                      their attributes for afterburn, etc.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Fixed reflecting the rocket jumper not retaining the
                      special rocket trail
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Fixed some reflected projectiles not retaining their
                      custom color attributes
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
